The pawpaw soup is a special and popular soup amongst the Tiv speaking tribe of Nigeria. The Tiv tribe is one of the largest minority ethnic groups in Nigeria with a population of nearly six million people residing in the middle belt states of Nigeria like Benue, Taraba, Nasarawa and Plateau. Some of the numerous health benefits of pawpaw include; its ability to reduce free radicals that contribute to cancer development and progression, thereby making it beneficial for cancer treatment and also to reduce cancer risk, it reduces the risk of heart disease, it also gives your skin a more youthful and toned look. You can eat it for lunch or dinner all year round. INGREDIENTS PREPARATION Your pawpaw soup is ready and can now be served hot with either Pounded Yam, Semovita, Eba or Fufu. 